# Core Logic Rules

## This directory is PURE TypeScript
- ZERO imports from 'react', 'next', or any DOM/browser API
- ZERO imports from 'node:fs', 'node:http', or any Node-specific module (except in tests)
- Every function is a PURE FUNCTION: same input → same output, no side effects
- Every function has JSDoc with @param, @returns, and @example
- Every module has a barrel export (`index.ts`)

## Testing
- Every file in `src/core/` MUST have corresponding tests in `src/core/__tests__/`
- Tests use Vitest (`describe`, `it`, `expect`)
- Tests use REAL data fixtures, not mocks
- Tests run with `npx vitest run src/core/`
- NO network calls in tests — everything is offline

## Type Safety
- TypeScript strict mode
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type guards if needed
- No type assertions (`as`) — use proper narrowing
- All function signatures fully typed (params + return)
- Use discriminated unions for classification results

## Classification Module Rules
- `preClassify()` runs FIRST — it catches ~60% of Lebanese headlines
- `scoreByKeywords()` runs SECOND — dictionary-based scoring
- `ensemble()` combines all signals with configurable weights
- The `classify()` barrel function orchestrates the pipeline
- DEFAULT classification is `neutre`, DEFAULT category is `neutre`
- OMBRE default category is `political_tension` (NOT cultural_event)
- LUMIERE default category is `institutional_progress`

## Deduplication Rules
- Title normalization: lowercase, strip URLs, strip punctuation (keep Arabic \u0600-\u06FF), collapse whitespace, first 80 chars
- Dedup key: `normalizedTitle + '-' + dateYYYYMMDD`
- Jaccard threshold: 0.6 for near-duplicates on the same day
- Priority: higher `SOURCE_PRIORITY` wins when merging
- Cross-language duplicates are NOT merged (Jaccard too low across scripts)
